message.content:
cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.AR

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on enhancing the security of systems through remote attestation schemes.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper proposes a new approach for runtime remote attestation that can be applied to any application regardless of its complexity.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are possible categories as the paper discusses the deployment of runtime remote attestation on complex systems, such as virtual machines in a cloud.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on hardware design, but rather on the development of a novel control-flow model for runtime remote attestation.
